annotationA: Ubiquitinyl hydrolase 1; Ubiquitin-specific protease activity; zinc ion binding; Lys48-specific deubiquitinase activity; omega peptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein deubiquitination; proteasome-mediated ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process; free ubiquitin chain depolymerization; protein K48-linked deubiquitination; neuron projection morphogenesis
annotationB: 26S proteasome non-ATPase regulatory subunit 14; Metalloprotease component of the 26S proteasome that specifically cleaves 'Lys-63'-linked polyubiquitin chains. The 26S proteasome is involved in the ATP-dependent degradation of ubiquitinated proteins. The function of the 'Lys-63'-specific deubiquitination of the proteasome is unclear (By similarity)
